The White House Office of Public Engagement and the National Space Council held a meeting with over 100 Latino science, technology, engineering, and mathematics (STEM) students and leaders from the space sector. The meeting aimed to discuss the Biden-Harris Administration's efforts to inspire, prepare, and employ the current and future space workforce, with a focus on ensuring opportunities for the Latino community. The meeting included speakers such as Federal Communications Commission (FCC) Commissioner Anna Gomez, who discussed the establishment of the FCC's Space Bureau and its role in advancing space equity, accessibility, and innovation. Other speakers highlighted the importance of an inclusive and representative workforce in the science field. Community leaders pledged to continue collaborating with the Biden-Harris Administration to expand Latino access and representation in space, STEM, and other areas.